.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fBTftpOption::option()\fR

.PP
Name and value of a TFTP option.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fB\fI{reject, Feature:: access() | TftpKey::string()}\fR\fR

.PP
Controls which features to reject. This is mostly useful for the server as it can restrict the use of certain TFTP options or read/write access.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fB\fI{callback, {RegExp ::string(), Module::module(), InitialState :: term()}}\fR\fR

.PP
Registration of a callback module. When a file is to be transferred, its local filename is matched to the regular expressions of the registered callbacks. The first matching callback is used during the transfer. See \fIread_file/3\fR and \fIwrite_file/3\fR.

.PP
The callback module must implement the \fItftp\fR behavior, see callbacks.

.PP
At the end of the list of callbacks there are always the default callbacks \fItftp_file\fR and \fItftp_binary\fR with the \fIRegExp = ""\fR and \fIInitialState = []\fR.

.PP
The \fIInitialState\fR should be an option list, and the empty list should be accepted by any callback module.  The \fItftp_file\fR callback module accepts an \fIInitialState = [{root_dir, Dir}]\fR that restrict local file operations to files in \fIDir\fR and subdirectories. All file names received in protocol requests, relative or absolute, are regarded as relative to this directory.

.PP
\fBWARNING: \fRThe default callback module configuration allows access to any file on any local filesystem that is readable or writable by the user running the Erlang VM.  This can be a security vulnerability. It is therefore recommended to explicitly configure the \fItftp_file\fR callback module to use the \fIroot_dir\fR option.


.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fB\fI{logger, module()}\fR\fR

.PP
Callback module for customized logging of errors, warnings, and info messages. The callback module must implement the \fItftp_logger\fR behavior. The default module is \fItftp_logger\fR.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fB\fI{max_retries, MaxRetries::non_neg_integer()}\fR\fR

.PP
Threshold for the maximal number of retries. By default the server/client tries to resend a message up to five times when the time-out expires.

.RE


